More generally, suppose that we have some smooth and proper \overline {X} over \operatorname {Spec} ( \mathbb {Z} ) \setminus  S, as well as a relative normal crossing divisor D;
let X be the general fibre of \overline {X} \setminus  D.
Then the realisation M_ { { \mathrm {cris}} \, \, p} is defined for p \not \in  S;
its most natural definition is given by the generalisation of the crystalline theory, considered by Faltings in [Fa, IV], to the "logarithmic poles" case.
